CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 27, 1954, pg. 21 reads: "Herron Hill P-TA Rallies to Keep Teen Canteen - Registration - Space limitations and supervision make it necessary to limit attendance to Herron Hill students. John Morgart, left, principal, is one of those volunteering service to keep project alive after school board cut out evening recreation in public schools.  Some 300 youngsters attend canteen each Friday."
TitMainTitle: Principal John Morgart, and three women, registering group of boys and girls for Teen Canteen in Herron Hill Junior High School
